Genitalia: Aedeagus in dorsal view (fig. 
11
) with sides subparallel, slightly dilated at ostium level, apical plate subtriangular with sides rectilinear, narrowly rounded at apex; in side view (fig. 
12
) slightly curved, robust, apex straight, rather narrow. Tegmen widely Y-shaped, dorsal part of ring membranous.
